General Martin Dempsey said he 'added to the grief' of Debbie Lee , whose son Marc was killed in Ramadi in August 2006 . 
  The 28-year-old was the first Navy SEAL to die in Iraq . 
  He said the city was 'not symbolic in any way' while discussing operations against ISIS . 
  Lee was outraged and wrote an open letter to the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff . 
  He apologized and said he regretted adding to her grief . 
  Lee's son was killed while providing covering fire in the city . 
 